    "liar_game_data": {
        "topic": "Arts & Creative Mix-ups",
        "question": "You want to talk about 'Painting' (Huìhuà). However, the word sounds exactly like 'Conversation'. How do you ensure the listener understands you are talking about art?",
        "options": [
            "Use Context / Objects (eg. 画画)",
            "Shout LOUDER",
            "Use a different tone",
            "There is no way"
        ],
        "correct_answer_index": 0,
        "explanation": "In Chinese, many words share the exact same sound and tones (Homophones). 绘画 (Painting) and 会话 (Conversation) both are 'Huìhuà'. Context is your best friend—mentioning brushes or galleries clarifies the artistic intent!"
    }
